  "market_context": "EURUSD 5-minute chart on 22/12/2023 showing a bearish breaker block forming after a high-low-higher high-lower low sequence, with a bearish fair value gap overlapping the breaker, creating a unicorn model setup around the 1.1024–1.1030 zone.",
  "key_observation": "The bearish breaker block overlaps with a bearish fair value gap, forming a unicorn model. Stop loss placed just above the breaker block achieves 2R quickly, while a stop at the swing high would have missed the take profit and been stopped out.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the bearish breaker pattern via the high-low-higher high-lower low sequence and mark the series of down-close candles as the breaker block.",
    "Step 2: Note displacement through the breaker creating a bearish fair value gap, which overlaps the breaker — confirming the unicorn model.",
    "Step 3: Define two possible entries: at the start of the fair value gap, or at the breaker within the fair value gap.",
    "Step 4: Compare two stop loss placements — one above the breaker block, one above the swing high — and project 2R targets for each.",
    "Step 5: Observe that the breaker-stop variant hits 2R quickly, while the swing-high-stop variant just misses take profit and gets stopped out."
  ],
  "outcome": "Stop placed above the breaker block reached 2R; stop placed at the swing high missed the take profit and was stopped out.",
  "lessons": "Placing the stop loss just above the breaker block (within the unicorn model) provides tighter risk and a more achievable 2R target than placing it at the wider swing high, where the same move would miss take profit and result in a loss.",
